    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-19T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-19T01:35:00-05:00" n="657"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/403: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-19T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >March 19, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>285. My 273, March 15. British Ministry is informed that March loadings in United
                    States of wheat destined for Iran will be very <pb facs="0624" n="612"
                        xml:id="pg_612"/> small. This is disturbing since Tehran is still living
                    from day to day and because it now appears that considerable part of the 30,000
                    tons for Iranian civil use will not arrive much before next harvest. To ease the
                    situation in June could not Department arrange for tankers returning from
                    Australia to bring back larger cargoes of wheat?</p>
                <p>I should appreciate receiving from Department by telegraph a statement of wheat
                    loadings from United States and Canadian ports for Iran monthly since November.
                    This is needed to check the conflicting statistics received locally from various
                    sources.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
